'''Evereska''' ({{Pronounce|eh|ver|EH|ska|refs=}}, [[Elvish]] for "fortress home") was a secreted city within a fabled valley in the [[Western Heartlands]], one of the last realms of the [[elves]] in the [[North]]. during the early years of the [[Era of Upheaval]]. It was the epitome of elven culture and beauty, and nearly no outsiders were considered welcome within.

{{Quote|When I rest at the end of the day and retreat into reverie...I recall the Evereska I wandered as a youth, when I followed a haunting song or a wisp of light among the roiling fogs of the [[Greycloak Hills|Greycloaks]], picked sweet berries in the hollows of the hills, and swam in the cold streams that flowed out of their heights.|[[Aedyn Graymantle]], wilderness guide and [[ranger]] of Evereska.}}

